A mediocre movie. Amazing how such a vast universe in the wrong hands has turned into something generic and lifeless. In an almost desperate attempt to please the 'fans' and undo the construction of the previous movie, JJ Abrams cowardly drives the movie into the comfort zone all the time, always trapped in the Manichean and nostalgic feeling of the old movies, without delving deeper or daring in no situation. A rotten script that presents equally obvious situations and resolutions, such that there is no room even for its (charismatic) characters to shine. In essence it is a movie to be forgotten in all respects (yes, not even the thousand nostalgic scenes have the impact they should) solely made to fulfill the table and generate a few more millions for the mouse company, congratulations.

Note: two stars in consideration to the cast that I have very affection. Daisy Ridley, Adam Driver, John Boyega, Oscar Issac, Carrie Fisher, thanks for trying so hard to do a good job, you deserved more
